Installation instructions on Debian
-----------------------------------
Concerto currently depends on the following OCaml libraries:

* Lwt
* Calendar
* Cryptokit
* Parsifal (available at https://github.com/ANSSI-FR/parsifal)

To compile Concerto, you also need the following tools:

* Make
* OCaml
* OCaml-findlib
* OCaml IDL

Therefore, to compile Parsifal, you need to get Parsifal, and ensure
you have the following packages installed:

 * git
 * make
 * ocaml
 * ocaml-findlib
 * camlidl
 * liblwt-ocaml-dev
 * libcalendar-ocaml-dev
 * libcryptokit-ocaml-dev

When they are installed, you can type in the following commands:
% cd <your_dev_dir>
% git clone https://github.com/ANSSI-FR/concerto
% cd concerto
% make


Notes
-----

The source code has been checked with Debian Jessie. In particular,
the used OCaml version is 4.01.